OL,3,CCooking oil contamination scandal
OL,4,Csparks outrage in China
OL,6,FThere is no suggestion that this
OL,7,Fscandal will challenge President Xi's
OL,8,Fposition but given he has spoken on
OL,9,Fthis matter so publicly and
OL,10,Femphatically, he will have ordered the
OL,11,Fstrictest of investigations, and
OL,12,Fcomprehensive monitoring of public
OL,13,Freaction.
OL,15,FChina does have national standards in
OL,16,Fplace which require edible oils to be
OL,17,Ftransported in dedicated containers
OL,18,Fbut there are no specific laws
OL,19,Fgoverning the practice.
